SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04537915
Version: 1

HPSBMU03230 rev.1 - HP Insight Control server deployment Remote Disclosure of
Information

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2015-01-12
Last Updated: 2015-01-12

Potential Security Impact: Reflected Cross-site Scripting (XSS), disclosure
of information

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP Insight
Control server deployment that could be exploited remotely resulting in
disclosure of information.

References:

CVE-2014-7881
SSRT101875

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP Insight Control server deployment - all versions

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2014-7881    (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:N/I:P/A:N)       4.3
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP has provided the following recommendation to resolve this vulnerability:
HP no longer supports the web interface for Insight Control server
deployment. HP recommends using the standard interface by updating to Insight
Control server provisioning. The white paper Data Migration from Insight
Control server deployment to Insight Control server provisioning at the
following location provides instructions on how to update Insight Control
server deployment to Insight Control server provisioning.
http://h17007.www1.hp.com/us/en/enterprise/servers/solutions/info-library/ind
ex.aspx?cat=insightmanagement&subcat=ic

HISTORY
Version:1 (rev.1) - 12 January 2015 Initial release

